                <head>246. Notes of a Special Group meeting, March 8<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d246fn1">Operational developments during the past week on the Cuba
                        project. Secret 1 p. <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>, DDO/<gloss
                            target="#t_LA_1">LA</gloss>/COG Files: Job 82–00679R, Box 3, Special
                        Group Mtgs—Cuba.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-03-08">March 8, 1961</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d246-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d246-1"/>
                <p>1. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName> noted that a meeting is
                    scheduled for Saturday morning to discuss broad policy aspects of this operation
                    with Mr. Bundy’s associates. He told the Group, however, about operational
                    developments during the past week, including the landing of the airplane in
                    Jamaica and the arrival of its nine-man crew in Miami. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName> also touched on the visit to the White
                    House of the Guatemalan emissary, and the reported threat that Guatemala would
                    proceed with its own anti-Castro activity if the U.S. did not move. He also
                    reported some progress in developing a cohesive political organization among the
                    Cuban exiles.</p>
            </div>
